An agent A claimed that the following lfs_fs_parent_match code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 17.8.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8 is A function parameter should not be modified.
Note that the object referred to by a pointer parameter may be modified, but the pointer itself shall not be modified.
</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of lfs_fs_parent_match.
```c
static int lfs_fs_parent_match(void *data,
        lfs_tag_t tag, const void *buffer) {
    struct lfs_fs_parent_match *find = data;
    lfs_t *lfs = find->lfs;
    const struct lfs_diskoff *disk = buffer;
    (void)tag;

    lfs_block_t child[2];
    int err = lfs_bd_read(lfs,
            &lfs->pcache, &lfs->rcache, lfs->cfg->block_size,
            disk->block, disk->off, &child, sizeof(child));
    if (err) {
        return err;
    }

    lfs_pair_fromle32(child);
    return (lfs_pair_cmp(child, find->pair) == 0) ? LFS_CMP_EQ : LFS_CMP_LT;
}
